description: Recladding and internal reconfiguration of existing building with extensions (3 upper floors to Clarence Street and full height extensions up to 9 storeys to the rear) to create 202 no. co-living units (sui generis) (in place of 64 no. student rooms (sui generis)) with retention of 4 no. ground floor commercial units (Class E), creation of new café (Class E) and co-working areas (Class E) at ground floor with internal and external residential amenity spaces, bike storage, refuse, disabled car parking, service yard and new basement plant room.

constraints_details.constraints_layer_description: PROPST P8a 107 -183 Clarence St, Station Bldgs, Fife Rd & Rear Yard
KEYACH Kingston Town Centre Key Area of Change

decision_conditions: The development hereby permitted shall begin before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.Reason: This is required by Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).
